 At Sun, 4 Dec 2005 18:20:04 -0500, ittaibalaban@gmail.com wrote:
 > Using drscheme 299.407 (the gcc3 binary) on
 > ubuntu 5.10.
 > Some entries (e.g. "Pretty Big") are too
 > wide, so there should be a horizontal scroll-
 > box.
 
 I'm assuming that you have not clicked "show details" and that when you
 say "too wide" you don't mean that the dialog is wider than the screen
 but rather the contents of the dialog are wider than the dialog itself.
 Is that right?
 
 The code is actually designed to make the dialog as wide as the widest
 language (when all tabs are turned down) so there is probably a bug
 somewhere. I don't suppose you can put a screenshot somewhere?
 
 Thanks,
 Robby
From: Robby Findler <robby@cs.uchicago.edu>
